Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present Yennora Logistics Estate, western Sydney’s newest industrial business park due for completion in Q1 2021.

+ Offering flexible building areas ranging from 10,000sqm* to 40,000sqm*
+ The warehouse can be accessed by multiple docks and on-grade roller shutter doors with a minimum warehouse height of 10m*
+ Close proximity to Yennora Train Station
+ B-Double access to Nelson Road and surrounding streets leading onto the Cumberland Highway and Hume Highway


Yennora is centrally located for last mile delivery and has undergone a major rejuvenation of the area within the past 24 months with the a high number of institutional ownership investing in upgrading the precinct. Yennora is home to the largest intermodal terminal in NSW and is home to some of the countries largest industrial occupiers.

This is your opportunity to position your business amongst local and national occupiers and being part of Sydney’s Last Mile.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: CENTRAL LOCATION WITH DIRECT FREIGHT ACCESS | YENNORA DISTRIBUTION CENTRE

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
On behalf of Stockland, CBRE is excited to offer a unique leasing opportunity at Yennora Distribution Centre (YDC), one of the largest distribution centres of its kind in the southern hemisphere. YDC features flexibility to accommodate long term growth with over 300,000sqm of warehouse space onsite.

This site also operations as an intermodal rail terminal allowing for quick and efficient distribution anywhere in Sydney, and is closely located to the M4 Motorway (6km), Great Western Highway (6km) and main arterial roads.

Building Features:
- Building 11 – 8,535 m² warehouse + 557 m² office
- 7 on-grade roller doors
- 77 car parking spaces
- 12 metre awning
- 10.0-13.25 metre internal warehouse clearance
- 38 metre hardstand truck court area
- 6 tonne point load warehouse slab floor
- K22 ESFR fire sprinkler system
- Direct rail access from Port Botany 
- Separate truck loading area to car parking
- Outdoor recreational area

Location Features:
- Zoned IN1 General Industrial
- Suitable for 24/7 operations 
- 25/26 metre B-Double approved access route
- Future expansion opportunities within estate

Sustainability Initiatives:
- Energy efficient LED lighting, grouped and programmable motion sensor controls, with photoelectric cells
- Rain water harvesting for reuse in landscape irrigation and toilet flushing
- Solar powered hot water services
- Translucent sheeting to 10% of the roof area to provide natural light to warehouse
- Pedestrian and cyclist end of trip facilities

Should you require any additional information or wish to arrange an inspection, please contact the exclusive leasing agents.

Yennora Distribution Centre is owned and managed by Stockland.

* all figures and measurements are approximate
